Description: wiki-ingest — remove OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH/_raw fallback
 Audit B1 (docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.2) flags
 `.skills/wiki-ingest/SKILL.md` line 62 as asserting that the raw
 staging area lives inside the vault (`OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH/_raw/`) with
 `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR` only as a fallback. In dual-zone mode `_raw/` is
 deliberately outside the vault — any skill falling back to
 `$VAULT_PATH/_raw/` resolves to a non-existent directory.
 .
 This patch rewrites the sentence so `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR` becomes the
 canonical (required, absolute) source of truth. Callers that previously
 relied on the implicit fallback must now configure `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR`
 explicitly, which is the correct behaviour for dual-zone deployments.
 .
 Composition with B2 : B2 touches line 64 of the same file (deletion
 safety). B1 and B2 are designed to compose sequentially (B1 first,
 then B2) with no hunk overlap.
